{
  "texts": [
    "Adaptability and learningCreating AI systems that adapt to changing user needs and environments is a critical challenge in HCAI, requiring advanced learning mechanisms and continuous user interaction.AI systems that continuously learn and improve from ongoing user interactions offer the potential for more personalized and effective human-AI collaboration.",
    "However, continuous learning also introduces risks, such as the potential for overfitting recent data or introducing biases as the system adapts to new information [34].",
    "Adaptivity and adaptability are solutions for enabling system modification when new needs arise during its use.",
    "Adaptivity is automatically determined by the system that tailors itself on the basis of repeated user interactions and habits; adaptability is determined by users, who are provided with tools to manually perform actions to tailor the system [53].",
    "Balancing the need for adaptability with the stability and reliability of the system is a crucial challenge."
  ]
}